info:
Thanks for setting up Node-RED with Seqera!

Here are some resources to get you started:

- [Node-RED tutorials](https://nodered.org/docs/tutorials/)
- [Seqera Node-RED YouTube Playlist](#) _(coming soon)_
- [Other Node-RED extensions](https://flows.nodered.org/)

You can find the Seqera nodes in the sidebar on the left, under the heading "Seqera".
To jump-start your development, take a look at the examples that come with the extension:

* Menu (top right `â‰¡` button)
* Import
* Examples (modal's left sidebar)
* @seqera/node-red-seqera dropdown
* Choose an example and import into your current workflow

These are designed to be drop-in automation flow chunks and can often be used together.

If you need help or would like to contribute, please check out the GitHub repository for this extension: https://github.com/ewels/node-red-seqera
